{"id":14195,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masashi_Tashiro","text":"=\"preserve\">Masashi Tashiro (\u7530\u4EE3\u307E\u3055\u3057, born August 31, 1956 in Saga Prefecture) is a former Japanese television performer and member of Japanese musical group Rats & Star. He was brought up in Shinjuku, Tokyo. On December 21, 2001, Tashiro was the first Japanese person chosen by the American magazine \"Time\" as \"Person of the Year\".\nTashiro was fired from the entertainment world in 2001 because of scandals.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"August_31","surface_form":"August 31","offset":41},{"uri":"1956","surface_form":"1956","offset":52},{"uri":"Saga_Prefecture","surface_form":"Saga Prefecture","offset":60},{"uri":"Japan","surface_form":"Japan","offset":89},{"uri":"Television","surface_form":"television","offset":98},{"uri":"Music","surface_form":"music","offset":142},{"uri":"Rats_%26amp%3B_Star","surface_form":"Rats & Star","offset":156},{"uri":"Shinjuku%2C_Tokyo","surface_form":"Shinjuku, Tokyo","offset":190},{"uri":"December_21","surface_form":"December 21","offset":210},{"uri":"2001","surface_form":"2001","offset":223},{"uri":"United_States","surface_form":"American","offset":281},{"uri":"Magazine","surface_form":"magazine","offset":290},{"uri":"Time_(magazine)","surface_form":"Time","offset":300},{"uri":"Person_of_the_Year","surface_form":"Person of the Year","offset":310},{"uri":"Entertainment","surface_form":"entertainment","offset":358},{"uri":"Scandal","surface_form":"scandal","offset":397}]}